This was the absolute WORST experience I have ever encountered when ordering from a restaurant. At 8:10 pm, I ordered a meal from this establishment by calling them directly, did not use Yelp. My meal arrived at my door at 9:50 p.m.. The delivery driver smelled of marijuana and appeared intoxicated. I left $1.32 tip (total was $26). The driver left and I opened my food and it was ice cold. I called the restaurant and notified them the food was cold, and spoke to someone who identified himself as Carlos, the manager. Carlos stated he would credit the cost of the food back to my account and if I ordered again, it would be at no cost. I hung up. As I was heating up my meal, I received phone calls from a number I did not know to my personal cellphone. I answered after the fourth call, and it was the driver calling to confirm I meant to leave just $1.32. I said yes, the food was almost two hours late. I then said "Do you know how inappropriate it is to call a customer's private cellphone to complain about gratuity?" He then shouted "GO FU*K YOURSELF" and began to threaten me. I hung up and immediately called the restaurant to report what happened. I was very scared by how aggressive the driver sounded. I spoke with Carlos again who apologized profusely. I asked for the drivers name and was told it was Fred. I called the 86th police precinct in Brooklyn to file a report and was told to contact the BBB. Today, two days after the original incident, I called back attempting to use the credit to order the same meal for lunch. I mentioned to the young lady who answered who I was and she said she remembered. After placing my order, she stated the credit would be $3 off. I protested, and a new manager came to the phone. This manager said she could not give me a free meal and that Carlos was a cashier, who did not have the authority to say what he said. She then said, "It's not my fault the driver is an AS*HOLE". I simply could not believe this. I did say right then that I was surprised a manager would choose this language, considering. I tried to protest and ask for at the very least- more of discount but she refused, then placed the order taker back on the phone who then accused me of "trying to start problems". I kept trying to speak and say how unprofessional the whole experience was, but she turned the entire incident around on me claiming I was trying to cause an issue when this was absolutely not the case. I hung up, very frustrated. I did just report this whole thing to the BBB as the police advised me to do. For $26, this is how you treat a customer (who has ordered previously many times)? I refuse to believe, "This is how it is in Brooklyn" as the excuse for why a business would behave in such a way. A true shame. I advise anyone with money to be very careful if they decide to order from here and to check who the driver on duty is. They are rude, and it is unsafe for someone that unhinged to have your home address. Best of luck if you do decide to order. Appalling, all the way around.
